    <note>Xiang(2) Gong [17321] He was poor and became a retainer (ke) of the Later Zhou emperors and rose to high office under Song, he was prefect of Henan fu for over ten years. Enfeoffed as Qinguo gong, it is hard to believe that he was not the person responsible for the later rise to distinction of his probable collateral kin (probably nephew), Minzhong [705]. The address given as Huaizhou, Henei was only a chroronym. CHECK funerary inscription by Wei Xiang. CBD, 1, 626.</note>
